Dear The Last Looks Podcast  and Mentors:

With great enthusiasm, here is my application to be mentored by makeup industry professionals from @the.lastlooks.podcast. 
My name is Pothmolita Dou but I’m better known as Apple. I’m a self-taught makeup artist from Cambodia who moved to America in 2017 after receiving a top 5 scholarship from Ve Neill to study at Cinema Makeup School in Los Angeles. I graduated in 2018 and have been working professionally since then. In the past 4 years I’ve worked on dozens of shorts, music videos, commercials, and student films, participated in IMATS as a competitor and as a demo artist, taught classes and workshops in my home country and even worked as the head department on a feature film. My specialties include cinema makeup, character design, sculpting, molding, spfx application, and beauty. 

I’m hoping that the Last Look Mentor program can help me take the next step in my career. Although I’ve been able to grow my technical ability largely on my own, I’ve found that working as a makeup artist requires much more than just application skill - among other things, it takes set presence, how to work with limited time and budget, problem solving, and managing a team. These are the types of skills that I’m hoping to improve through this professional mentorship opportunity. I think I would also benefit greatly by learning from the insights of an expert who has already successfully navigated the industry. 

If you take a glance at my profile you’ll notice that I’m truly passionate about my job and about makeup. This mentorship program seems like a unique opportunity to help me not only grow as a professional myself but also to give back to some of the students and makeup artists that I support. 

Thank you

Modern Yak'heney យក្ខេនីសម័យ
ការថតរូបបែបសិល្បះ
Inspired by Cambodian Lakhon Khorl mask dance, This icy mask is sculpted mold and cast with modern material to create a new touch to my root. 
Lakhon Khol is a traditional mask theatre performance of Cambodia that had its origins during the Angkor period. It is believed to have begun during the 10th century through the inscription K.99 Sambor Prei Kuk temple in the reign of King Jayavarman V.
It very important for me to keep using my culture touch imbedded into my art. Khmer is in me and I’m proud. 

 love 
 Apple

Process of the making Yakheney Mask !
Inspired by Lakhorn Khorl mask dance in Cambodia meet with futurism ! 
Mask sculpted on Ed head @monstermakersus 
Molded use @smoothon 
Cast with Crystal  clear resin 202@smoothon 
It’s my firs time casting with this material so I want able to make the mask completely clear as I wanted to due to the air bubble. But I’m so happy with how the mask turn out .
Next I’ll be trying to cast this in metal color or gold to show more texture and details.

❌💥🚨💊🔺Warning Rashes and fake rash makeup . 

Come up with solution to create realistic bumps of rashes 
I want to create rashes flacky skin. With few hours to prepare I created sheet of baldiez with silicon bumps to create realistic makeup on @jacobestrada2029 .

Step 1 brush / airbrush thine layer of Baldiez 
I use super baldiez from @smoothon 
Spread a thin layer on smooth surface , can be plastic tray or metal tray ( I use vasalin as an release , spread thine vasalin on surface ahead of time on the tray) 

Step2 drop little drop of silicon . I use dragon skin and tinted it with flocking in red pinky color. 
Create the parttern of the rash. Silicon will move but itself and creat perfect round shape when gelling .

Step 3 . Wait around 10mn till the silicon almost set and Use poking tool to poke on the silicon to created bumpy texture .

Step4. Wait till silicon dry and brush on another layer of baldiez 

Step5 . Removethe piece with powder. Store the pieces on foam sheet and makes sure to use a lot of powder on it . 
Application was only 1h and it was amazingly fast and easy . The baldiez was great and easy to blend. 

This technique work out great for me coz I didn’t want to free hand and dot the latex or 3degree on set and wait for it to dry. 
Hope this technique help. I was so proud of myself to come up with this on my own. 🤣🤣🤣. 

Few thing I wish I do better is to take more time apply the pieces so it wouldn’t wrinkle as much but it work for the time and the lighting that we was shooting. I also feel like I should tint the silicone less red .

🥰enjoy

Department of provincial training give  free education for special skills to young teens in my hometown stung treng province . I get to spend time with students that are learning those beauty skills makeup hair and nails. There were 50 students in the class today. I had a lot of fun sharing my story and my makeup journey with them. 
I hope I get to do this every years. 
For demo I shared with them the skill to match medium and deep complexion. Cambodian women are told that they need to be white so often time the make up trend is to whiten the skin tone with much lighter complextion foundation.I hope one days women in my country understand that they are just beautiful just the way they are. I’m so glad I get to do this work shop 🥰

Hanuman is a revered heroic figure in Khmer history in southeast Asia. He features predominantly in the Reamker, a Cambodian epic poem, based on the Sanskrit Itihasa Ramayana epic.Intricate carvings on the walls of Angkor Wat depict scenes from the Ramayana including those of Hanuman.

In Cambodia and many other parts of southeast Asia, mask dance and shadow theatre arts celebrate Hanuman with Ream (same as Rama of India). Hanuman is represented by a white mask. Particularly popular in southeast Asian theatre are Hanuman's accomplishments as a martial artist Ramayana.
